# Tailwind Best Practices

- Prefer utility composition in markup; avoid ad-hoc CSS unless necessary.
- Use design tokens from `tailwind.config` (spacing, colors, typography), not arbitrary values.
- Group classes consistently: layout, spacing, typography, visual, state.
- Avoid long unreadable class chains; extract reusable UI primitives/components.
- Use `@apply` sparingly and only in shared semantic component layers.
- Keep responsive behavior mobile-first and explicit by breakpoint.
- Ensure color contrast and focus states meet accessibility expectations.
- Avoid conflicting utilities that hide intent (`p-2 p-4`, multiple text sizes).
- Keep dark mode strategy consistent (`class` or `media`) across the app.
